== 人口 ==
根據2001年人口普查，[[印度教徒|印度教徒]]佔全邦人口的68.57%，[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]佔14.5%，基督教徒佔4.5%。<ref name="Indian Census 2001 - Religion">{{Cite web |url=http://demotemp257.nic.in/httpdoc/Census_Data_2001/Census_data_finder/C_Series/Population_by_religious_communities.htm |title=Indian Census 2001 – Religion |access-date=2015-02-10 |archive-date=2007-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070312153215/http://demotemp257.nic.in/httpdoc/Census_Data_2001/Census_data_finder/C_Series/Population_by_religious_communities.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Kerala-not-Goa-has-maximum-no-of-Christians/articleshow/2649158.cms |title=存档副本 |access-date=2015-02-10 |archive-date=2021-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513003800/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/kerala-not-goa-has-maximum-no-of-christians/articleshow/2649158.cms |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==语言==
该邦官方语言为[[印地语|印地语]]及[[乌尔都语|乌尔都语]]<ref>[http://nclm.nic.in/shared/linkimages/NCLM50thReport.pdf Report of the Commissioner for linguistic minorities: 50th report (July 2012 to June 2013)] {{Wayback|url=http://nclm.nic.in/shared/linkimages/NCLM50thReport.pdf |date=20160708012438 }} Commissioner for Linguistic Minorities, Ministry of Minority Affairs, Government of India</ref>。其他主要语言包括：[[孟加拉语|孟加拉语]]、[[桑塔利语|桑塔利语]]、[[奥里亚语|奥里亚语]]、[[迈蒂利语|迈蒂利语]]、[[库鲁克语|库鲁克语]]及[[霍语|霍语]]等<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bihardays.com/jharkhands-11-second-languages-will-create-new-jobs-enrich-national-culture/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2017-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106033703/http://www.bihardays.com/jharkhands-11-second-languages-will-create-new-jobs-enrich-national-culture/ |archive-date=2014-01-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。


